variables.name: FontFamily/primaryFontFamily
variables.description: primary naming was chosen for this variable name based on how many instances of this typeface shows up on Bild homepage. This was measured with the Project Wallace analyzer tool.

variables.name: FontFamily/secondaryFontFamily
variables.description: secondary naming was chosen for this variable name based on how many instances of this typeface show up on Bild homepage. This was measured with the Project Wallace analyzer tool.

variables.name: FontFamily/tertiaryFontFamily
variables.description: tertiary naming was chosen for this variable name based on how many instances of this typeface shows up on Bild homepage. This was measured with the Project Wallece analyzer tool.

variables.name: FontWeight/700BlackFontWeight
variables.description: 700 is considered black weight because Gotham Condensed is the primary font family (most used in headlines). In other font families 700 is not black weight but bold.

variables.name: BILD/elevations/scrim-70
variables.description: This is used as a background overlay for most high priority alert messages that block the user from proceeding, forcing the user to take an action.

variables.name: BILD/elevations/shadow-60
variables.description: Used on elevation effects.

variables.name: BILD/greens/BILDGreen040
variables.description: This value of green was found in a text field's text color.

variables.name: BILD/grays/BILD085-50
variables.description: The 50% opacity on this color makes it equivalent to BILD093.

variables.name: BILD/sentiments/BILDBlue
variables.description: This Blue color was taken from the Weather 2024 project.

variables.name: Core/coreColorPrimary
variables.description: This red color is Bild's main brand color. It remains constant across Light and Dark Mode.

variables.name: Core/coreColorSecondary
variables.description: This white color is Bild's secondary brand color. This variable changes across Light and Dark Mode.

variables.name: Core/coreColorTertiary
variables.description: This dark grey color is Bild's tertiary brand color. This variable changes across Light and Dark Mode.

variables.name: Core/coreColorSecondaryConstant
variables.description: Use this on elements that must maintain the white color even in dark mode.

variables.name: Core/coreColorTertiaryConstant
variables.description: Use this on elements that need to maintain the dark color across themes and color modes.

variables.name: Semantic/Attention/accentColorPrimary
variables.description: Bild's accent color is the same as its primary color. In some dark mode elements this color changes to white. This is often used on small elements such as accordion arrows that change color when they change state or hover states that use some red on them in light mode.

variables.name: Semantic/Attention/accentColorPrimaryConstant
variables.description: Use this token when you don't want small accents to change color in dark mode. This is often used on small elements such as accordion arrows that change color when they change state or hover states that use some red on them in light mode.

variables.name: Semantic/Attention/attentionColorSuccess
variables.description: Fills and strokes use this for grabbing attention and communicating the sentiment of success.

variables.name: Semantic/Attention/attentionColorLow
variables.description: This color variable is currently used in marketing content dedicated to the BildPur subscription. It can be used in other elements that need to grab the user's attention.

variables.name: Semantic/Attention/attentionColorMedium
variables.description: This color variable is currently used in Bild's horizontally scrolling breaking news headline content. It can be used in other elements that need to grab the user's attention.

variables.name: Semantic/Attention/attentionColorHigh
variables.description: This color variable is the same as Bild's core brand color. This color has been used in marketing content dedicated to subscriptions and in warning messages found in the subscription process. It can be used in other elements that need to grab the user's attention.

variables.name: Semantic/Border/borderColorMediumContrast
variables.description: This is the most used color for separators across Bild products.

variables.name: Semantic/State/colorPrimaryActive
variables.description: Use this token for most components that have a hover state. The word active in this design system is used interchangeably with the word hover and pressed. Since hover states do not exist on mobile devices the choice was made to use the word active for representing hover and pressed states.

variables.name: Semantic/State/colorSecondaryActive
variables.description: Use this token for when a component is interacted with and a state change needs to be indicated.

variables.name: Semantic/State/colorSecondaryActiveInverse
variables.description: Use this token for when a component is interacted with and a state change needs to be indicated with the use of color.

variables.name: Semantic/State/colorTertiaryActive
variables.description: Use this token for when a component is interacted with and a state change needs to be indicated.

variables.name: Semantic/Surface/surfaceColorTertiaryInverse
variables.description: This surface color was found on the warning message for logging in with unidentified user or password data.

variables.name: Semantic/Surface/surfaceColorPrimaryGradient
variables.description: Used next to sliders buttons and slider container edges for fading out content.

variables.name: Semantic/Surface/surfaceColorTertiaryGradient
variables.description: Used on skeletons.

variables.name: Semantic/Text/textColorSecondary
variables.description: This is used on article image source mainly.

variables.name: Component/Alert/alertSurfaceColor
variables.description: On marketing offer surfaces this variable is not used. The alertSurfaceConstant variables should be used.

variables.name: Component/Alert/alertSurfaceColorConstant
variables.description: On marketing offer surfaces this variable is not used. The alertSurfaceConstant variables should be used.

variables.name: Component/Hey/heySeparator
variables.description: This is the most used color for separators across Bild products.

variables.name: Semantic/Icon/iconColorInverse
variables.description: Uses same as separator neutral tone color. Is lighter tone than iconColor in Dark mode.

variables.name: Semantic/Icon/iconColorConstant
variables.description: Uses same as separator neutral tone color. Is lighter tone than iconColor in Dark mode.

variables.name: Component/Label/labelColorPrimary
variables.description: This variable references Bild015 in light mode and Bild093 in dark mode.

variables.name: Component/Label/labelColorPrimaryInverse
variables.description: This variable references Bild015 in light mode and Bild093 in dark mode.

variables.name: Component/Label/labelColorPrimaryConstant
variables.description: Use this when label color needs to remain constant between light & dark mode. This token references Bild015.

variables.name: Component/Label/labelColorPrimaryInverseConstant
variables.description: Use this when label color needs to be constant between light and dark mode. This token references the primitive Bild093.

variables.name: Component/MenuItem/menuItemLabelColorSecondary
variables.description: The variable can be used on secondary menus that many times show up on dedicated home pages specific to a topic. The menu labels are often times using the color white across color modes.

variables.name: Component/Menu/menuScrolledSurfaceGradient
variables.description: Used on a thin part at the top of header in navigation menu.

variables.name: Component/!MultitextLinks/!multitextLinksBgIdle
variables.description: !do not use! these variables have been deprecated and multitext link buttons are now classified as partner buttons.

variables.description: !do not use! these variables have been deprecated and multitext link buttons are now classified as partner buttons.

variables.name: Component/!MultitextLinks/!multitextLinksBorderActive
variables.description: !do not use! these variables have been deprecated and multitext link buttons are now classified as partner buttons.

variables.name: Component/!MultitextLinks/!multitextLinksContainerBorder
variables.description: !do not use! these variables have been deprecated and multitext link buttons are now classified as partner buttons.

variables.name: Component/Selection/selectionBorderColor
variables.description: Checkboxes and Radio buttons use this variable for their border.

variables.name: labelTextSurfaceColorPrimaryPrimitiveName
variables.description: This variable is only for use in Figma's Design System File. It is automating some of the content in documentation pages.

variables.name: labelTextColorMode
variables.description: This is currently for use in this design system's documentation texts. It is a text string made for being used in light and dark mode documentation texts.

variables.name: Button/ContentGapSpace

variables.name: Button/LabelFontSize
variables.description: These variables were made to experiment with how scaling space could work across different content scaling / size / contrast themes.

variables.name: Semantic/Layout/Grid/Fluid/PagenInlineSpace
variables.description: This variable is used for making teaser images have zero inline (side) paddings on mobile and Tablet devices.

variables.name: Semantic/Layout/Section/sectionSpaceMD
variables.description: desktop matches live site, mobile given more spacing

variables.name: Semantic/Typography/FontSize/Kicker/Kicker3FontSize
variables.description: Values come from comparing NMT Figma File 01_Foundation to online CSS. Online kickers are numbered from 0 to 3.

variables.name: Semantic/Typography/FontSize/Kicker/Kicker4FontSize
variables.description: Values come from comparing NMT Figma File 01_Foundation to online CSS. Online kickers are numbered from 0 to 3.

variables.name: Semantic/Typography/LineHeight/Body/bodyTextLineHeight
variables.description: Figma's font line height currently does not allow for multipliers as is used on current website css var(--body-line-height)

variables.name: Semantic/Typography/LetterSpacing/letterSpacingNegativeXS
variables.description: This letter spacing was only found in large titles on iOS mobile app large title component.

variables.name: Component/Article/Typography/articleImageCaptionFontSize
variables.description: NMT CSS --article-figure-meta-font-size

variables.name: Component/Article/Size/articleGalleryATeaserWidth
variables.description: same as standard teaser width size variable

variables.name: Component/Avatar/Size/AvatarBorderRadius
variables.description: For avatarCorners prioritize the use of percentage value 100% instead of pixel values.

variables.name: Component/Images/articleImageSourceFontSize
variables.description: NMT CSS --article-figure-meta-font-size

variables.name: Component/Menu/menuItemFontSize
variables.description: This variable is used on the menu link lane and on the mobile side menu drawer.

variables.name: Component/LargeTitle/largeTitleFontSize
variables.description: html class stage-block-title__text css var --ressort-header-font-size(sm-md-lg)

variables.name: Component/Newsticker/newsTickerTimeFontSize
variables.description: same as kicker3

variables.name: Component/Separators/SeparatorsPremiumAlertFontSize
variables.description: Values come from comparing NMT Figma File 01_Foundation to online CSS. Online kickers are numbered from 0 to 3.

variables.name: Component/LargeTitle/largeTitle&ArrowInlineSpace
variables.description: This variable is used on large title headings that are h2 elements in html and indicate a new section in the user interface. This space changes when a user hovers over the large title.

variables.name: Component/LargeTitle/largeTitle&ArrowInlineSpaceActive
variables.description: This variable is used for increasing the space between the text and the arrow at the end of the large title text. On mobile devices there is no hover state so this variables values are the same as the default state values.

variables.name: Component/Newsticker/newsTickerTimeLineHeight
variables.description: Figma currently does not allow for percentages in Line Height variables. The values in this token are the result of multiplying the font size by the line height variable defined on the Bild home css -> newsTickerTime line height: 1.3. Line height for this component does not change across devices.

variables.name: Component/Teaser/badgeInnerStackSpace
variables.description: This space variable is used for creating the top and bottom space between a badge's text label and the surface that the text label is on top of.

variables.name: Component/Teaser/badgeInnerInlineSpace
variables.description: This space variable is used for creating the left and right space between a badge's text label and the badge background surface that the text label is on top of.

variables.name: Component/Teaser/badgeSubscription&VideoMarginSpace
variables.description: This variable is used for creating space around the outside of a subscription badge or video icon badge.

variables.name: Component/Teaser/badgeStdTeaserSubscription&VideoMarginSpace
variables.description: This variable is used for creating space around the outside of a subscription badge or video icon badge.

variables.name: Component/Teaser/standardTeaser/standardTeaserWidthSize
variables.description: variable used for css class stage-teaser standard teaser article width at different device width previews

variables.name: Component/_DSysDocs/bildDesignFrameSpace
variables.description: Variable used in spacing parameters of bild.design webpage mockups. move to bild.design group maybe
